    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-14T11:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-14T11:30:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.917/5694: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stewart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-14T10:30:00-06:00"
                            >December 14, 1943—10:30 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 17—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–513. For the Foreign Economic Administration.<note n="31" xml:id="d258fn1">The
                        Office of Economic Warfare (formerly the Board of Economic Warfare) was
                        consolidated into the Foreign Economic Administration, September 25,
                        1943.</note> Reference Department’s circular airgram of November 13, 1943,
                    12:10 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d258fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_131">p. 131</ref>.</note> and
                    Department’s circular telegram of December 10, 10 a.m.<note n="33"
                        xml:id="d258fn3">Not printed.</note> Also Department’s circular airgram of
                    November 13, 1943, 12:20 p.m.<note n="33" xml:id="d258fn4">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Country Agency states that in view of certain discrepancies caused by local
                    banking regulations affecting commodities exportable from the United States
                    under general license, it will require import recommendations for all
                    commodities exported to this country. The <pb facs="0279" n="267"
                        xml:id="pg_267"/> following is quoted from the Country Agency’s letter of
                    December 10, 1943 to the Embassy: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“…<note n="35" xml:id="d258fn5">Omission indicated in the original
                                airgram.</note> please take notice that effective immediately all
                            commodities that have been withdrawn from the Decentralization Plan
                            including those commodities listed in Export Bulletin No. 125,<note
                                n="36" xml:id="d258fn6">Issued by the Office of Exports of the
                                Office of Economic Warfare.</note> will be subject to Import
                            Recommendations.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>A verbal exception to this requirement was received to wit newsprint and orders
                    for $25.00 or less.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
